The paper focuses on improving the robustness of deep neural networks for object classification under occlusion, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces prototype learning, attention regulation, and feedback connections, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques, such as attention maps, which could place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which could place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
